 Billionaire investor and Captain of the Super Eagles, Ahmed Musa has identified the ability to recognize opportunities of secured investments as key to wealth creation, stating that Nigerians should take decisive steps to invest in reputable organizations where their investments would yield the desired growth while the capital is also secured. Musa, whose net worth is put at $18 million Dollars, gave the hint when he paid an investment visit to Cosgrove Smart Estate at the weekend in Abuja. While he identified Cosgrove as a secured investment destination for diligent investors, who desire lucrative yield on capital, as well as guaranteed security of investment, Musa commended Cosgroveâ€™s ability to sustain Research and Development as well as apply the findings, stating that the organisation has been able to sustain innovation. 